This app contains the search command "dbdata", which polls data from a REST API.
 © 2018 Manish Sharma

Contact: sharmama@dnb.com
Source: NA

Syntax

  | dbdata <url> <paramMap>? <output>? <timeout>? <headers>? <realm>? <useAppCre>? <data>? <ref>?
  
Option TYPE: pattern

  url string: http://my_rest_api/endpoint
  
  paramMap string: param1=val1, param2=val2
  
  output string: json || text (default: json)
  
  timeout int: 0..∞

  headers json: {'option1': 'val1', 'option2': 'val2'}
  
  realm string: realm1
  
  ref string: callref
  
  useAppCre boolean: True || False (default: True)
  
  data string: data

Examples

| curl url="https://reqres.in/api/users" ref=text1
-- Returns the data from the endpoint as json(default) along with text1 as input reference.

| curl url="https://api.github.com/user" realm="realm1" output=text
-- Basic login at the Github API with response as plain text. Please use realm field to use saved password in REST lookup.


| curl url="http://influx:3000/api/datasources/proxy/1/query" paramMap="db=statsdemo, q=show tag keys" headers="{'Authorization': 'Bearer <token>'}" useAppCre=False
-- Access InfluxDB with authorization token not stored in app
